  "title": "E-anatum 06 (RIME 1.09.03.06 composite)",
  "language": "sumerian",
  "translation_source": "ORACC ETCSRI — CC BY-SA 3.0",
  "source_url": "https://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/etcsri/Q001058",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(i 1) For Nanše , E-ana-tum built the city-wall of Lagaš and had it manned ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.6",
      "line_range": "6",
      "translation": "(i 6) E-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , whose name was proclaimed by Enlil , given strength by Ninĝirsu , chosen by Nanše in the heart , nourished on rich milk by Ninhursaĝa , called by a propitious name by Inana , given wisdom by Enki , beloved of Dumuzid-Abzu , supported by Hendursaĝ , child of Aya-kurgal , ruler of Lagaš , restored Ĝirsu for Ninĝirsu . He built the city-wall of Irikug . He built Niĝin for Nanše ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.37",
      "line_range": "37",
      "translation": "(iii 11) E-ana-tum defeated Elam , the marvelous mountain range and piled up a burial mound for it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.42",
      "line_range": "42",
      "translation": "(iii 16) He defeated Arawa , whose ruler marched with its standard in the vanguard and piled up a burial mound for it ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.48",
      "line_range": "48",
      "translation": "(iv 2) He defeated Umma , and piled up 20 burial mounds for it . He returned Ninĝirsu's beloved field , the Gu-edena , under his control ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.56",
      "line_range": "56",
      "translation": "(iv 10) He defeated Unug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.58",
      "line_range": "58",
      "translation": "(iv 12) He defeated Urim ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.60",
      "line_range": "60",
      "translation": "(iv 14) He defeated Ki-Utu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.62",
      "line_range": "62",
      "translation": "(iv 16) He conquered Iriaz and killed its ruler ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.66",
      "line_range": "66",
      "translation": "(v 1) He conquered Mišime ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.68",
      "line_range": "68",
      "translation": "(v 3) He destroyed Arua ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.70",
      "line_range": "70",
      "translation": "(v 5) All lands trembled before E-ana-tum , whose name was proclaimed by Ninĝirsu ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.75",
      "line_range": "75",
      "translation": "(v 10) In the year when the king of Akšak rebelled , E-ana-tum , whose name was proclaimed by Ninĝirsu , repelled him from the Antasura of Ninĝirsu until Akšak and destroyed ( his city ) ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.85",
      "line_range": "85",
      "translation": "(vi 6) E-ana-tum then dug a new canal for Ninĝirsu . ...."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.92",
      "line_range": "92",
      "translation": "(vii 2) The personal god of E-ana-tum , who ... of Ninĝirsu , is Šul-MUŠxPA ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001058.95",
      "line_range": "95",
      "translation": "(vii 5) E-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , child of Aya-kurgal , ...."
    }
  ],
